spec: as3286
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(asyncio)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/asyncio.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/asyncio.html"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source code"
    - "any proprietary source"
  notes:
    - "Wave 666 (as3286): __iadd__, __isub__, __imul__ dict-presence (in-place augmented assignment) for asyncio types."
    - "All values verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13."
    - "Classes covered: asyncio.Task, asyncio.Future, asyncio.Event, asyncio.Lock, asyncio.Semaphore, asyncio.BoundedSemaphore, asyncio.Condition, asyncio.Queue, asyncio.PriorityQueue, asyncio.LifoQueue."
    - "Key finding (__iadd__): all 10 asyncio classes return false for __iadd__. In-place addition (__iadd__, +=) is the augmented assignment variant of __add__. asyncio types define no __add__ (confirmed false in wave 658), so __iadd__ is equally absent. asyncio.Event/Lock/Condition are boolean-state synchronization guards; += has no meaning for synchronization state objects. asyncio.Semaphore/BoundedSemaphore manage an integer permit counter fully encapsulated behind acquire()/release() coroutines; the counter is not exposed for in-place arithmetic. asyncio.Task/Future are pending coroutine result handles; in-place addition is undefined for coroutine handles. asyncio.Queue/PriorityQueue/LifoQueue are ordered item stores with no augmented arithmetic data model."
    - "Key finding (__isub__): all 10 asyncio classes return false for __isub__. In-place subtraction (__isub__, -=) is the augmented assignment variant of __sub__. asyncio types define no __sub__ (confirmed false in wave 658), so __isub__ is equally absent. asyncio synchronization primitives (Event, Lock, Condition, Semaphore, BoundedSemaphore) have no numeric data model that -= could operate on. asyncio.Task/Future: coroutine result handles; -= is not defined. asyncio.Queue/PriorityQueue/LifoQueue: item stores; in-place subtraction is entirely absent."
    - "Key finding (__imul__): all 10 asyncio classes return false for __imul__. In-place multiplication (__imul__, *=) is the augmented assignment variant of __mul__. asyncio types define no __mul__ (confirmed false in wave 658), so __imul__ is equally absent. Note: list defines __imul__ (list *= n repeats in-place), but asyncio queue types are not list subclasses and implement no list-repetition protocol. asyncio.Event/Lock/Condition/Semaphore/BoundedSemaphore: synchronization primitives with no in-place multiplication semantics. asyncio.Task/Future: coroutine result handles; *= is not defined. asyncio.Queue/PriorityQueue/LifoQueue: queue types do not define __imul__; they manage items solely through put()/get() coroutine calls."
    - "Continues the all-false run from wave 656 (__call__/__len__/__getitem__) through wave 666 (__iadd__/__isub__/__imul__) — eleven consecutive waves of 100% false results for asyncio types."
    - "Cross-wave summary for asyncio subjects:"
    - "  Wave 656 (as3136): __call__/__len__/__getitem__ — all false for all 14."
    - "  Wave 657 (as3151): __setitem__/__delitem__/__contains__ — all false for all 14."
    - "  Wave 658 (as3166): __add__/__sub__/__mul__ — all false for all 14."
    - "  Wave 659 (as3181): __truediv__/__floordiv__/__mod__ — all false for all 14."
    - "  Wave 660 (as3196): __pow__/__lshift__/__rshift__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 661 (as3211): __and__/__or__/__xor__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 662 (as3226): __radd__/__rsub__/__rmul__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 663 (as3241): __rtruediv__/__rfloordiv__/__rmod__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 664 (as3256): __rpow__/__rlshift__/__rrshift__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 665 (as3271): __rand__/__ror__/__rxor__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 666 (as3286): __iadd__/__isub__/__imul__ — all false for all 10."
  created_at: "2026-04-13"

error_model: python_exceptions

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# __iadd__ dict-presence — operator.contains(Cls.__dict__, '__iadd__')
#
# All 10 asyncio classes return false for __iadd__.
# In-place addition (__iadd__, +=) is the augmented assignment variant of __add__.
# asyncio types define no __add__ (wave 658), so __iadd__ is equally absent.
# asyncio.Event/Lock/Condition: boolean-state synchronization guards;
#   obj += n is not a defined Python operation for these types.
# asyncio.Semaphore/BoundedSemaphore: permit-counter objects; the counter
#   is fully encapsulated behind acquire()/release() coroutines. The internal
#   integer state is not exposed for += operations.
# asyncio.Task/Future: pending coroutine result handles; in-place addition
#   is undefined for coroutine handles.
# asyncio.Queue/PriorityQueue/LifoQueue: ordered item stores with no
#   augmented arithmetic or repetition data model.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

