# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# __imul__ dict-presence — operator.contains(Cls.__dict__, '__imul__')
#
# All 10 asyncio classes return false for __imul__.
# In-place multiplication (__imul__, *=) is the augmented assignment variant of __mul__.
# asyncio types define no __mul__ (wave 658), so __imul__ is equally absent.
# Note: list defines __imul__ (list *= n repeats the list in-place), but
#   asyncio queue types are not list subclasses and implement no such protocol.
# asyncio.Event/Lock/Condition/Semaphore/BoundedSemaphore: synchronization
#   primitives with no in-place multiplication semantics of any kind.
# asyncio.Task/Future: coroutine result handles; *= is not defined.
# asyncio.Queue/PriorityQueue/LifoQueue: queue types manage items through
#   put()/get() coroutine calls only — no __imul__ is defined.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

